#: ../../N/nugry.rst:9
msgid ""
"[Usenet, ‘newbie’ + ‘-gry’] n. A :ref:`newbie` who posts a :ref:`FAQ` in the"
" rec.puzzles newsgroup, especially if it is a variant of the notorious trick"
" question: \"Think of words ending in ‘gry’. Angry and hungry are two of "
"them. There are three words in the English language. What is the third "
"word?\" In the newsgroup, the canonical answer is of course ‘nugry’ itself. "
"Plural is nusgry /n[y]oos´gree/."
msgstr ""
"[Usenet、‘newbie’ + ‘-gry’] 名詞。rec.puzzlesニュースグループに\\ :ref:`FAQ`\\ を投稿する\\ "
":ref:`newbie`\\ "
"。特にそれが有名なひっかけ問題の変種である場合。「‘gry’で終わる単語を考えよ。angryとhungryはそのうちの二つだ。英語には三つの単語がある。三つ目の単語は何か?」ニュースグループでの定番の答えは、もちろん‘nugry’それ自体である。複数形はnusgry"
" /n[y]oos´gree/。"

#: ../../N/nugry.rst:16
msgid "adj. Having the qualities of a nugry."
msgstr "形容詞。nugryの性質を持つ。"
